HEADWORD: Sotto voce
<hw>Sot`to vo"ce</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[It.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>With a restrained voice or moderate force; in an
undertone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Spoken low or in an undertone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sou</ent>⟦br⟧
